What insurance do I like?
Automotive insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible claims, involves a significant expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be provided or use, among others.
Having a car is the main one.
It is that, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the appropriate car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a disaster.
The premium is the insurance price, which is based on a variety of factors, such as age, sex, seniority of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
For this reason, people over 25 years of age and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of loss due to their caution.
Similarly, using the censuses, the companies concluded that married persons tend to have less accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
These are many of the variables that insurers take into account when determining the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best adapts to his profile.
Here we will set out the most significant variables when choosing either type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an accessible price, as may be the low experience in driving and seniority of the driver's licence.
Although the ideal for being well assured is risk-free insurance, other more cost-effective options exist.
The most foreseeable drivers can opt for free risk insurance so that they get coverage from insurance at any risk but at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the client pays part of the amount of the disaster.
"The portion of the amount of the disaster that the client pays will be based on the value of the premium, which will be higher than the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the client provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A advice.
If you are a 25-year-old minor, try to be careful and avoid claims to the extent possible, since this will affect the subsidy, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"Bonifications and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonus, "Noguera clarifies.
Beyond the 25 years it becomes easier for drivers when making a contract with insurance, since the rate of claims is reduced thanks to the experience accumulated.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose an all-risk insurance with franchise.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the pre-acquired experience after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is preferable that he or she negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his or her economic situation allows him or her to do so.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be people with the lowest rate of claims, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be free-of-risk insurance (up to EUR 300), or extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of premium.
"They have a more casual conduct and they have a greater purchasing power to allow the luxury to assume a greater amount of franchises," Justice Luis Noguera.
For pensioners an insurance at any risk with a franchise is preferable (by being the one of EUR 150), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of subsidy.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible claims, but also because it represents an important expenditure, that is why it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
